Sentencas: This study compares the electrochemical performance of the composite cathodes of La(0.6)Sr(0.4)CoxFe(1-x)O(3-delta) and BaZr0.8Yb0.2O3-delta (BZYb) sintered at 900 and 1100 degrees C in anode-supported protonic ceramic fuel cells (PCFCs) using a BZYb electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt content on electrochemical performance for La0.6Sr0.4CoxFe1-xO3-δ and BaZr0.8Yb0.2O3-δ composite cathodes in protonic ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: For materials composited with BZYb, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF), La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC), and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-delta (LSF) were used.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt content on electrochemical performance for La0.6Sr0.4CoxFe1-xO3-δ and BaZr0.8Yb0.2O3-δ composite cathodes in protonic ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The composite cathodes sintered at 1100 degrees C showed higher per-formance than those sintered at 900 degrees C, because the number and thickness of proton conductive network paths of BZYb within the composite cathodes increase with increasing sintering temperature.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt content on electrochemical performance for La0.6Sr0.4CoxFe1-xO3-δ and BaZr0.8Yb0.2O3-δ composite cathodes in protonic ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The PCFCs with LSCF-BZYb, LSC-BZYb, and LSF-BZYb composite cathodes exhibit power densities of 0.25, 0.19, and 0.07 W cm(-2), respec-tively, at an operating temperature of 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt content on electrochemical performance for La0.6Sr0.4CoxFe1-xO3-δ and BaZr0.8Yb0.2O3-δ composite cathodes in protonic ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the Co-free LSF-BZYb composite cathodes is originally higher than those of the Co-containing LSC-BZYb and LSCF-BZYb cathodes, suggesting that Co plays an important role in obtaining high catalytic activity for cathode reactions in PCFCs as well as con-ventional solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt content on electrochemical performance for La0.6Sr0.4CoxFe1-xO3-δ and BaZr0.8Yb0.2O3-δ composite cathodes in protonic ceramic fuel cells
